content:
Human-Labeled Majority-voted Examples:
Example 1:
Text: It would be better to have this discussion on the TKD talk page. Why don't you re-post it there?
Annotation: 14

Example 2:
Text: No, I didn't know that. Where does this "rule" come from?
Annotation: 9

Example 3:
Text: Indef-blocked. Any idea whose sock this is?
Annotation: 14

Example 4:
Text: I have reverted your relocation of the images of this fragment - as I think it better if the images and transcripts can be seen side-by-side.  Do you agree?
Annotation: 17

Example 5:
Text: <url> and <url> seem to be two articles on the same subject.  What's the point of having separate articles?
Annotation: 7

Example 6:
Text: I just reverted your addition of a fossil range template to <url>, because with only an arrow at the very right it didn't seem to add much useful information. Perhaps we could make a separate template to show only the Cenozoic or so, which would allow us to show more detail in these fossil ranges?
Annotation: 13

Example 7:
Text: Done. Comments?
Annotation: 12

Example 8:
Text: I'm sorry, but I'm unlikely to have time to help. Maybe try <url>?
Annotation: 15

Example 9:
Text: Hello, sorry I probably should have asked first, but I thought it might be a good idea to nominate one of the images you uploaded, <url>, for featured picture. I hope you don't mind me taking the liberty, as it were?
Annotation: 16

Example 10:
Text: I deleted the redirects <url> and <url> that were a result of the page moves.  Is that all you needed?
Annotation: 10
Imputed Majority-voted Examples:
Example 1:
Text: I haven't uploaded any more to Wiki because they tend to be more detailed and rather more abstruse. Have you had a look at Barry Burnham's book from Oxbow of 2004?
Annotation: 12

Example 2:
Text: Yes, that's fine, especially with the smaller sections. Where will they be posting their topic ideas?
Annotation: 12

Example 3:
Text: Need help with EF 175 via email. Mind <url> so we can discuss?
Annotation: 12

Example 4:
Text: Is there really any serious debate that Mobile IE is remotely comparable to Safari mobile? What source would be acceptable to show this?
Annotation: 12

Example 5:
Text: I'm pretty sure there already is a filter (possibly more than one) for this. What page got moved?
Annotation: 12

Example 6:
Text: As another aside, they are mostly Germans.  What's up with that?
Annotation: 3

Example 7:
Text: i took the photo, and if the kludgy licensing template would allow me to license i would. do you actually fix things or tag spam?
Annotation: 12

Example 8:
Text: I reverted <url> as it complicated my normal routine archiving of all the discussions on my talk page.  Could you please refrain from this kind of edit in future?
Annotation: 16

Example 9:
Text: Are the remaining IPs on <url> still a problem? If so is Tom dealing with it?
Annotation: 12

Example 10:
Text: Okay. Meanwhile, can you think of a good line for a <url> submission?
Annotation: 16
Now you will make your prediction (if you are unsure, just give your best estimate.) Your output should be an integer label:
Text: This is not a suitable candidate for CSD as it asserts notability. May I suggest you consider a <url>?
Annotation:
If you output anything other than a single integer (and absolutely nothing else, including explanatory text), your output will invalidate the dataset. So, please only output a single integer.
